fciOspfVpRouterDeadInterval.name: fciOspfVpRouterDeadInterval
fciOspfVpRouterDeadInterval.description: OSPF VP router dead interval. The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network. This parameter defaults with the value '40'.

fciOspfVpPollInterval.name: fciOspfVpPollInterval
fciOspfVpPollInterval.description: OSPF VP poll interval. The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non-broadcast multi-access neighbor. This parameter defaults with the value '120'.

fciOspfVpAuthenticationKey.name: fciOspfVpAuthenticationKey
fciOspfVpAuthenticationKey.description: OSPF VP authentication key. The Authentication Key. If the Area's Authentication Type is simplePassword, and the key length is shorter than 8 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. When read, ospfIfAuthKey always returns an Octet String of length zero. This parameter defaults with the value '0000000000000000h'.

fciOspfNeighborsTable.name: fciOspfNeighborsTable
fciOspfNeighborsTable.description: OSPF Neighbors Table. The OSPF Neighbors Table describes all neighbors in the locality of the subject router. Each entry contains the information regarding a single neighbor.

fciOspfNeighborIpAddress.name: fciOspfNeighborIpAddress
fciOspfNeighborIpAddress.description: Neighbor IP address. The IP address of this neighbor.

fciOspfNeighborStatus.name: fciOspfNeighborStatus
fciOspfNeighborStatus.description: Status. The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciOspfNeighborEligibleStatus.name: fciOspfNeighborEligibleStatus
fciOspfNeighborEligibleStatus.description: Neighbor eligible status. This parameter indicates whether the neighbor is eligible for DR election.

fciOspfAreasTable.name: fciOspfAreasTable
fciOspfAreasTable.description: The OSPF Area Data Structure contains informations regarding the various areas. The interfaces and the virtual links are configured as part of these areas. Area 0.0.0.0, by definition, is the Backbone Area. Each entry describes the configured parameters of one of the router's attached areas.

fciOspfAreaId.name: fciOspfAreaId
fciOspfAreaId.description: Area id. A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. This parameter defaults to the value '0.0.0.0' which is used to identify the OSPF backbone.

fciOspfAreaStatus.name: fciOspfAreaStatus
fciOspfAreaStatus.description: Status. The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciOspfAreaAuthType.name: fciOspfAreaAuthType
fciOspfAreaAuthType.description: Area authentication type. The authentication type specified for an area. This parameter defaults to the 'none' value and can take the value 'simplePassword' to enable authentication into the area.

fciOspfAreaStubStatus.name: fciOspfAreaStubStatus
fciOspfAreaStubStatus.description: Area stub status. This parameter indicates whether the area is a stub area or not.

fciOspfAreaStubMetric.name: fciOspfAreaStubMetric
fciOspfAreaStubMetric.description: Area stub metric. The OSPF metric associated to the stub area.

fciOspfAreaRangesTable.name: fciOspfAreaRangesTable
fciOspfAreaRangesTable.description: OSPF Address Range Table. The Address Range Table acts as an adjunct to the Area Table ; It describes those Address Range Summaries that are configured to be propagated from an Area to reduce the amount of information about it which is known beyond its borders. A range of IP addresses is specified by an IP address/IP network mask pair. For example, Class B address range of X.X.X.X with a network mask of 255.255.0.0 includes all IP addresses from X.X.0.0 to X.X.255.255.

fciOspfAreaRangeIpAddress.name: fciOspfAreaRangeIpAddress
fciOspfAreaRangeIpAddress.description: Area range IP address. The IP Address of the Net or Subnet indicated by the range.

fciOspfAreaRangeIpMask.name: fciOspfAreaRangeIpMask
fciOspfAreaRangeIpMask.description: Area range IP mask. The Subnet Mask that pertains to the Net or Subnet.

fciOspfAreaRangeStatus.name: fciOspfAreaRangeStatus
fciOspfAreaRangeStatus.description: Status. The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciOspfAreaRangeAreaId.name: fciOspfAreaRangeAreaId
fciOspfAreaRangeAreaId.description: Area range area id. The Area the Address Range is to be found within.

fciOspfAreaRangeRestrict.name: fciOspfAreaRangeRestrict
fciOspfAreaRangeRestrict.description: Restriction. The value 'off' indicates that intra-area LSAs that fall within the specified range are not advertised into other areas as inter-area routes. Instead, the specified range are advertised as summary network LSAs. The value 'on' specifies that the summary network LSAs are not advertised.

fciOspfVirtualLinksTable.name: fciOspfVirtualLinksTable
fciOspfVirtualLinksTable.description: OSPF Virtual Link Table. The Virtual Link Table describes the virtual links that the OSPF Process is configured to carry on.

fciOspfVlNeighborId.name: fciOspfVlNeighborId
fciOspfVlNeighborId.description: VL neighbor id. The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

fciOspfVlTransitAreaId.name: fciOspfVlTransitAreaId
fciOspfVlTransitAreaId.description: VL transit area id. The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0.

fciOspfVlStatus.name: fciOspfVlStatus
fciOspfVlStatus.description: Status. The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciOspfVlDRPriority.name: fciOspfVlDRPriority
fciOspfVlDRPriority.description: VL DR priority. The priority of this virtual link. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their router id as a tie breaker. This parameter defaults to the value '1'.

fciOspfVlTransitDelay.name: fciOspfVlTransitDelay
fciOspfVlTransitDelay.description: VL transit delay. The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link-state update packet over this interface.

fciOspfVlRetransmitInterval.name: fciOspfVlRetransmitInterval
fciOspfVlRetransmitInterval.description: VL retransmit interval. The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round-trip.

fciOspfVlHelloInterval.name: fciOspfVlHelloInterval
fciOspfVlHelloInterval.description: VL hello interval. The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

fciOspfVlRouterDeadInterval.name: fciOspfVlRouterDeadInterval
fciOspfVlRouterDeadInterval.description: VL router dead interval. The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

fciOspfVlAuthenticationKey.name: fciOspfVlAuthenticationKey
fciOspfVlAuthenticationKey.description: VL authentication key. If Authentication Type is simplePassword, the device will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. When read, ospfVifAuthKey always returns a string of length zero.

fciOspfAseExportInterval.name: fciOspfAseExportInterval
fciOspfAseExportInterval.description: ASE flow packets interval. Together with fciOspfAseExportLimit, controls the rate at which Autonomous System External (ASE) routes are imported. The rate is defined as the ratio of fciOspfAseExportLimit and fciOspfAseExportInterval, in number of routes per second. By default, ASE routes are imported at the rate of 100 ASEs per second.

fciOspfAseExportLimit.name: fciOspfAseExportLimit
fciOspfAseExportLimit.description: ASE flow packets limit. Together with fciOspfAseExportInterval, controls the rate at which Autonomous System External (ASE) routes are imported. The rate is defined as the ratio of fciOspfAseExportLimit and fciOspfAseExportInterval, in number of routes per second. By default, ASE routes are imported at the rate of 100 ASEs per second.

fciOspfAseExportStaticsMetric.name: fciOspfAseExportStaticsMetric
fciOspfAseExportStaticsMetric.description: Statics ASE export metric. The default metric (or cost) used by OSPF when propagating (exporting) routes learned via other protocols.

fciOspfAseExportStaticsTag.name: fciOspfAseExportStaticsTag
fciOspfAseExportStaticsTag.description: Statics ASE export tag. The OSPF tag to be placed on all routes exported by OSPF. Specifies one way of generating OSPF tags.

fciOspfAseExportStaticsType.name: fciOspfAseExportStaticsType
fciOspfAseExportStaticsType.description: Statics ASE export type The OSPF external routes type used to export static routes. The value '1' indicates that the metric of the static routes exported are directly comparable with OSPF metric. The value '2' indicates the contrary.

fciOspfAseExportRipMetric.name: fciOspfAseExportRipMetric
fciOspfAseExportRipMetric.description: RIP ASE export metric. The default metric (or cost) used by OSPF when propagating (exporting) routes learned via other protocols.

fciOspfAseExportRipTag.name: fciOspfAseExportRipTag
fciOspfAseExportRipTag.description: RIP ASE export tag. The OSPF tag to be placed on all routes exported by OSPF. Specifies one way of generating OSPF tags.

fciOspfAseExportRipType.name: fciOspfAseExportRipType
fciOspfAseExportRipType.description: RIP ASE export type The OSPF external routes type used to export RIP routes. The value '1' indicates that the metric of the static routes exported are directly comparable with OSPF metric. The value '2' indicates the contrary.

fciEgpAdminStatus.name: fciEgpAdminStatus
fciEgpAdminStatus.description: The value of this object indicates whether EGP (Exterior Gateway Protocol) is enabled or not. fciEgpNeighborTable must contain at least one entry. The default value is 'off'.

fciEgpAutonomousSystemNumber.name: fciEgpAutonomousSystemNumber
fciEgpAutonomousSystemNumber.description: The value of this object defines the autonomous system to which belongs this IP router. The authorized values are '1..65534'. The default value is '1'.

fciEgpStaticRoutesDistribution.name: fciEgpStaticRoutesDistribution
fciEgpStaticRoutesDistribution.description: The value of this object indicates whether EGP distributes static entries of the routing table (i.e., those defined in fciIpRouteTable) or not.. The autonomous systems to which these routing informations are distributed are defined in fciEgpTargetAsDistributionTable. The default value is 'off'.

fciEgpRipRoutesDistribution.name: fciEgpRipRoutesDistribution
fciEgpRipRoutesDistribution.description: The value of this object indicates whether EGP distributes entries of the routing table learnt by RIP (Routing Information Protocol) or not. The autonomous systems to which these routing informations are distributed are defined in fciEgpTargetAsDistributionTable. The default value is 'off'.

fciEgpMetricDistribution.name: fciEgpMetricDistribution
fciEgpMetricDistribution.description: The value of this object is the value indicated in the transmitted EGP datagrams concerning routing information learnt by RIP. The authorized values are '1..255'. The default value is '128'.

fciEgpNeighborTable.name: fciEgpNeighborTable
fciEgpNeighborTable.description: This table defines the EGP neighbors with witch EGP exchanges routing informations.

fciEgpNeighborIpAddress.name: fciEgpNeighborIpAddress
fciEgpNeighborIpAddress.description: The value of this object is the IP address of an EGP neighbor. This IP address must be a valid host address. The default value is '0.0.0.0'.

fciEgpNeighborStatus.name: fciEgpNeighborStatus
fciEgpNeighborStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciEgpNeighborAsNumber.name: fciEgpNeighborAsNumber
fciEgpNeighborAsNumber.description: The value of this object defines the autonomous system to which belongs this EGP neighbor. The authorized values are '1..65534'. The default value is '1'.

fciEgpTargetAsDistributionTable.name: fciEgpTargetAsDistributionTable
fciEgpTargetAsDistributionTable.description: As defined by fciEgpStaticRoutesDistribution and fciEgpRipRoutesDistribution, when EGP distributes static entries or entries of the routing table learnt by RIP (Routing Information Protocol), this table defines to which autonomous systems these entries are to be distributed. Only neighbors of an automous system specified in this table will receive these routing informations.

fciEgpTargetAsNumber.name: fciEgpTargetAsNumber
fciEgpTargetAsNumber.description: The value of this object identifies an autonomous system containing routers to which EGP distributes the routing informations. This AS must exist in fciEgpNeighborTable. The authorized values are '1..65534'. The default value is '0'.

fciEgpTargetAsStatus.name: fciEgpTargetAsStatus
fciEgpTargetAsStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciSnmpCommunityStringReadOnly.name: fciSnmpCommunityStringReadOnly
fciSnmpCommunityStringReadOnly.description: The value of this object is the string which identifies the 'public' community. The managers of this community have only 'read-only' access rights even on the objects with read-write access. The SNMP agent of this equipment compares the community string of a received GetRequest or GetNextRequest to this value to know whether it makes a GetResponse or not. This value may contain up to 14 printable characters. The default value is 'public'.

fciSnmpCommunityStringReadWrite.name: fciSnmpCommunityStringReadWrite
fciSnmpCommunityStringReadWrite.description: The value of this object is the string which identifies the 'administrator' community. The managers of this community have complete access rights (i.e. they have the rights which are defined in the MIB). The SNMP agent of this equipment compares the community string of a received GetRequest, GetNextRequest or SetRequest to this value to know whether it makes a GetResponse or not. This value may contain up to 14 printable characters. The default value is 'private'.

fciSnmpCommunityStringTrap.name: fciSnmpCommunityStringTrap
fciSnmpCommunityStringTrap.description: The value of this object is the string which identifies the 'alarm' community. The managers of this community may filter the received Traps according of this community string. The SNMP agent of this equipment sets the community string of all the sent Trap to this value. It sends traps to the managers defined in fciSnmpManagerTable. This value may contain up to 14 printable characters. The default value is 'private'.

fciSnmpAuthenticationFailureTrap.name: fciSnmpAuthenticationFailureTrap
fciSnmpAuthenticationFailureTrap.description: The value of this object specifies whether the SNMP agent sends the authenticationFailure trap or not. When enabled, this trap is sent with each reception of an unauthorized SNMP request (erroneous community string or manager not authorized). It can be useful to disable this sending when unauthorized SNMP managers polls very often the SNMP agent because the quantity of authenticationFailure trap is then very important and prevents the 'good' manager to show correctly the significant traps. The default value is 'off'.

fciSnmpModule0TrapSourceAddrVpId.name: fciSnmpModule0TrapSourceAddrVpId
fciSnmpModule0TrapSourceAddrVpId.description: The SNMP agent of module 0 indicates, as the source address of each TRAP, the IP address associated with the virtual port identified by this value. This virtual port must exist in fciVirtualPortTable. The authorized values are '0..199'. The default value is '0'.

fciSnmpModule1TrapSourceAddrVpId.name: fciSnmpModule1TrapSourceAddrVpId
fciSnmpModule1TrapSourceAddrVpId.description: The SNMP agent of module 1 indicates, as the source address of each TRAP, the IP address associated with the virtual port identified by this value. This virtual port must exist in fciVirtualPortTable. The authorized values are '0..199'. The default value is '255' meaning 'empty value' (blank value on the equipment configurator).

fciSnmpModule2TrapSourceAddrVpId.name: fciSnmpModule2TrapSourceAddrVpId
fciSnmpModule2TrapSourceAddrVpId.description: The SNMP agent of module 1 indicates, as the source address of each TRAP, the IP address associated with the virtual port identified by this value. This virtual port must exist in fciVirtualPortTable. The authorized values are '0..199'. The default value is '255' meaning 'empty value' (blank value on the equipment configurator).

fciSnmpManagerFiltering.name: fciSnmpManagerFiltering
fciSnmpManagerFiltering.description: The value of this object specifies whether the SNMP agent answers to all the SNMP managers or only to those defined in fciSnmpManagerTable. When set to 'on' the SNMP agent sends an authenticationFailure trap (if enabled) each time it receives a request from a manager not in the table. The default value is 'off' (i.e., no filtering : access for all managers)..

fciSnmpManagerTable.name: fciSnmpManagerTable
fciSnmpManagerTable.description: This table contains the SNMP managers to which SNMP traps may be sent. This table is also used to define the authorized managers when fciSnmpManagerFiltering is set to 'on'.

fciSnmpManagerIpAddress.name: fciSnmpManagerIpAddress
fciSnmpManagerIpAddress.description: The value of this object is the IP address of an SNMP manager. This IP address must be a valid host address. The default value is '0.0.0.0'.

fciSnmpManagerStatus.name: fciSnmpManagerStatus
fciSnmpManagerStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciSnmpManagerSendTraps.name: fciSnmpManagerSendTraps
fciSnmpManagerSendTraps.description: The value of this object specifies whether the SNMP agent sends the traps to this SNMP manager or not. The default value is 'on'.

fciSnmpManagerTrapsUdpPort.name: fciSnmpManagerTrapsUdpPort
fciSnmpManagerTrapsUdpPort.description: The value of this object indicates the UDP port to which are sent the SNMP traps. This value must be the value used by this SNMP manager when it listens for SNMP traps. The authorized values are '0..65535'. The default value is '162'.

fciBootPClientStart.name: fciBootPClientStart
fciBootPClientStart.description: The value of this object identifies start mode of equipement. The default value is 'no'.

fciBootPClientServer.name: fciBootPClientServer
fciBootPClientServer.description: The value of this object identifies server name. This value may contain up to 64 printable characters. The default value is an empty string.

fciBootPClientBootFile.name: fciBootPClientBootFile
fciBootPClientBootFile.description: The value of this object identifies generic name of bootfile. This value may contain up to 64 printable characters. The default value is an empty string.

fciBootPClientBootTime.name: fciBootPClientBootTime
fciBootPClientBootTime.description: The value of this object identifies time to wait before bootp launching. Time is specified in seconds. The authorized values are '15..900'. The default value is '180'.

fciBootPClientRetransNb.name: fciBootPClientRetransNb
fciBootPClientRetransNb.description: The value of this object identifies numbers of retransmissions of bootrequest packet. The authorized values are '0..10'. The default value is '5'.

fciBootPInterfaceTable.name: fciBootPInterfaceTable
fciBootPInterfaceTable.description: This table describes the parameters of BootP Virtual Ports. It offers a solution to link many servers on the bootp client or relay.

fciBootPInterfaceVpId.name: fciBootPInterfaceVpId
fciBootPInterfaceVpId.description: The value of this object identifies one virtual port. The default value is '255'.

fciBootPInterfaceIpAddress.name: fciBootPInterfaceIpAddress
fciBootPInterfaceIpAddress.description: The value of this object is the IP address associated to one bootp interface. The default value is '255.255.255.255'.

fciBootPInterfaceStatus.name: fciBootPInterfaceStatus
fciBootPInterfaceStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the entry of this table. The default value is 'valid'. It must be set to 'invalid' to delete the entry.

fciBootPInterfaceType.name: fciBootPInterfaceType
fciBootPInterfaceType.description: The value of this object indicates the fonctionnality of the equipement. The authorized values are 'client' or 'relay'. The default value is 'client'.

fciTelnetMaxSession.name: fciTelnetMaxSession
fciTelnetMaxSession.description: Maximum number of telnet session that the equipment would accept. This number include the telnet session issuing from the equipment. The modification of this parameter need a reboot of the equipment. The default value is 6.

fciTelnetTimer.name: fciTelnetTimer
fciTelnetTimer.description: This parameter is global to all connection and set the timer that make a session to be disconnected if no traffic is send or receive in the telnet session. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections

fciTelnetPwdP0.name: fciTelnetPwdP0
fciTelnetPwdP0.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 0 level. All the user set to a priority 0 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'root'.

fciTelnetPwdP1.name: fciTelnetPwdP1
fciTelnetPwdP1.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 1 level. All the user set to a priority 1 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP2.name: fciTelnetPwdP2
fciTelnetPwdP2.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 2 level. All the user set to a priority 2 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP3.name: fciTelnetPwdP3
fciTelnetPwdP3.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 3 level. All the user set to a priority 3 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP4.name: fciTelnetPwdP4
fciTelnetPwdP4.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 4 level. All the user set to a priority 4 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP5.name: fciTelnetPwdP5
fciTelnetPwdP5.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 5 level. All the user set to a priority 5 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP6.name: fciTelnetPwdP6
fciTelnetPwdP6.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 6 level. All the user set to a priority 6 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP7.name: fciTelnetPwdP7
fciTelnetPwdP7.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 7 level. All the user set to a priority 7 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP8.name: fciTelnetPwdP8
fciTelnetPwdP8.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 8 level. All the user set to a priority 8 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetPwdP9.name: fciTelnetPwdP9
fciTelnetPwdP9.description: This parameter set the password to access to a priority 9 level. All the user set to a priority 9 level have to uses this password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections The default value is 'user'.

fciTelnetUserStatus.name: fciTelnetUserStatus
fciTelnetUserStatus.description: This parameter set the status of the raw

fciTelnetUserLogin.name: fciTelnetUserLogin
fciTelnetUserLogin.description: This parameter set the login identification of the user. The password ask to the user would the associated priority password. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections.

fciTelnetUserPriority.name: fciTelnetUserPriority
fciTelnetUserPriority.description: This parameter associate a priority level to a user. The priority level give access right to different service. The default value is set to the lower priority level. The modification of the parameter takes effect after a hot reset and is used for new connections.

fcxRoutType20PacketBroadcasting.name: fcxRoutType20PacketBroadcasting
fcxRoutType20PacketBroadcasting.description: Diffusion des paquets IPX de type 20

fcxRoutCircType20PacketBroadcasting.name: fcxRoutCircType20PacketBroadcasting
fcxRoutCircType20PacketBroadcasting.description: Diffusion des paquets IPX de type 20

fmeTrblEventType.name: fmeTrblEventType
fmeTrblEventType.description: The value of this object is the cause of the system starting.

fmeTroubleReportInfoTable.name: fmeTroubleReportInfoTable
fmeTroubleReportInfoTable.description: This table contains the additional information about the trouble report. It's the fatal error zone : the snapshot of the memory and registers when there is a trouble. It contains the registers state, the system stack ...

fmeTrblInfoIndex.name: fmeTrblInfoIndex
fmeTrblInfoIndex.description: The value of this object identifies one and only one element of the trouble report.

fmeTrblInfoData.name: fmeTrblInfoData
fmeTrblInfoData.description: The value of this object is the data of this element of the trouble report.

fmeFamilyTable.name: fmeFamilyTable
fmeFamilyTable.description: This table contains general information about the families of the outstanding events. For one family, the maximum number of stored events is 6, but all the families can store simultaneously at most 3 events. So, the maximum number can fluctuate following the busy memory. When one event is added to the list of one family, the oldest event is kept in memory, and the event is added at the end of the list, with the possibility of a rotation of the stored events if there is no free memory.

fmeFamFamilyId.name: fmeFamFamilyId
fmeFamFamilyId.description: The value of this object identifies one and only one family.

fmeFamStoredEventsCount.name: fmeFamStoredEventsCount
fmeFamStoredEventsCount.description: The value of this object how many events are stored for this family.

fmeFamStoredEventsCommand.name: fmeFamStoredEventsCommand
fmeFamStoredEventsCommand.description: The value of this object permits, when it is set to 'delete', to destroy the stored events of this family. The equipment answers always with the value 'ready' to a GetRequest on this object.

fmeEventTable.name: fmeEventTable
fmeEventTable.description: This table contains the stored outstanding events.

fmeEvtFamilyId.name: fmeEvtFamilyId
fmeEvtFamilyId.description: The value of this object identifies one and only one family. This is the family this outstanding event belongs to.

fmeEvtEventIndex.name: fmeEvtEventIndex
fmeEvtEventIndex.description: The value of this object identifies one and only one outstanding event of this familty.

fmeEvtEventType.name: fmeEvtEventType
fmeEvtEventType.description: The value of this object is the event type. See the management function manual for more information on the description of the events.

fmeEvtTime.name: fmeEvtTime
fmeEvtTime.description: The value of this object is the value of sysUpTime when this event was stored.

fmeEvtLineId.name: fmeEvtLineId
fmeEvtLineId.description: The value of this object is the identifier of the line where this event takes place. The value '255' means 'general' (i.e., not a particular line).

fmeEvtData.name: fmeEvtData
fmeEvtData.description: The value of this object contains additional data for this event.

fmeTrapLineId.name: fmeTrapLineId
fmeTrapLineId.description: The value of this object is the identifier of the line where the event takes place. The value '255' means 'general' (i.e., not a particular line). This object is only used in a Trap PDU and is not accessible by GET requests.

fmeTrapFamilyId.name: fmeTrapFamilyId
fmeTrapFamilyId.description: The value of this object identifies one and only one family. This is the family the outstanding event belongs to. This object is only used in a Trap PDU and is not accessible by GET requests.

fmeTrapEventType.name: fmeTrapEventType
fmeTrapEventType.description: The value of this object is the event type. See the management function manual for more information on the description of the events. This object is only used in a Trap PDU and is not accessible by GET requests.

fmeTrapEventData.name: fmeTrapEventData
fmeTrapEventData.description: The value of this object contains additional data for the event. This object is only used in a Trap PDU and is not accessible by GET requests.

fmsCtrlStatus.name: fmsCtrlStatus
fmsCtrlStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the processing state of the statistics. The value 'notInProgress' indicates that there is only a SNMP access at the management function. The value 'InProgress' indicates that there is an access to the management function which is not a SNMP access.

fmsCtrlSumming.name: fmsCtrlSumming
fmsCtrlSumming.description: The value of this object is the summing mode of the statistics. The value 'infinite' indicates that the statistics are calculated since the last counters reset. With the value 'notInfinite', the statistics are calculated on the configurable period, which there is an automatic counters reset beyond. The default value is 'notInfinite'.

fmsCtrlCountersCommand.name: fmsCtrlCountersCommand
fmsCtrlCountersCommand.description: The value of this object permits, when it is set to 'reset', to re-initialize all the counters except those in fmStatEthOutputTrafficTable, fmStatEthInputTrafficTable and fmStatEthManagementTable. The equipment answers always with the value 'ready' to a GetRequest on this object.

fmsCtrlResetTime.name: fmsCtrlResetTime
fmsCtrlResetTime.description: The value of this object is the value of sysUpTime when the counters were re-initialized by a 'reset' command (see fmsCtrlCountersCommand).

fmsGlobInitBuffCount.name: fmsGlobInitBuffCount
fmsGlobInitBuffCount.description: The value of this object is the total number of the buffers created when initializing.

fmsGlobFreeBuffCount.name: fmsGlobFreeBuffCount
fmsGlobFreeBuffCount.description: The value of this object is the total number of the free buffers.

fmsGlobCpuA.name: fmsGlobCpuA
fmsGlobCpuA.description: The value of this object is the maximum instant load of the CPU A on all the modules.

fmsGlobCpuB.name: fmsGlobCpuB
fmsGlobCpuB.description: The value of this object is the maximum instant load of the CPU B on all the modules.

fmsGlobVcInUseCount.name: fmsGlobVcInUseCount
fmsGlobVcInUseCount.description: The value of this object is the number of the virtual circuits established.

fmsGlobGeneratorsInUseCount.name: fmsGlobGeneratorsInUseCount
fmsGlobGeneratorsInUseCount.description: The value of this object is the number of the busy traffic generators.

fmsGlobCompressOctetGain.name: fmsGlobCompressOctetGain
fmsGlobCompressOctetGain.description: The value of this object is the total gain, in volume (in bytes), generated by the compression/scrambling function.

fmsGlobCompressBillGain.name: fmsGlobCompressBillGain
fmsGlobCompressBillGain.description: The value of this object is the total gain, in billing (in segments), generated by the compression/scrambling function.

fmsGlobLanCpu.name: fmsGlobLanCpu
fmsGlobLanCpu.description: The value of this object is the transputer CPU load.

fmsGlobCongCpuLostBlocks.name: fmsGlobCongCpuLostBlocks
fmsGlobCongCpuLostBlocks.description: Nb de blocs de 0 a N octets rejetes sur congestion CPU (N = 160 en v2.1)

fmsGlobCongRamLostBlocks.name: fmsGlobCongRamLostBlocks
fmsGlobCongRamLostBlocks.description: Nb de blocs de 0 a N octets rejetes sur congestion memoire (N = 160 en v2.1)

fmsInputDataPktsCounter.name: fmsInputDataPktsCounter
fmsInputDataPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the data packets received by the internal switch from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsInputDataBytesCounter.name: fmsInputDataBytesCounter
fmsInputDataBytesCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the data bytes received by the internal switch from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsInputIntrPktsCounter.name: fmsInputIntrPktsCounter
fmsInputIntrPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the interrupt packets received by the internal switch from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsInputReinitPktsCounter.name: fmsInputReinitPktsCounter
fmsInputReinitPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the reset packets received by the internal switch from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsInputCallPktsCounter.name: fmsInputCallPktsCounter
fmsInputCallPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the call packets received by the internal switch from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsInputCallConfPktsCounter.name: fmsInputCallConfPktsCounter
fmsInputCallConfPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the call confirmation received and successfully processed by the internal switch from the beginning of the collection period. This object is therefore the number of the virtual circuits established from the beginning of the collection period.

fmStatLineTable.name: fmStatLineTable
fmStatLineTable.description: This table contains the information about the statistics by line.

fmsLineId.name: fmsLineId
fmsLineId.description: The value of this object is the one line identifier.

fmsLineState.name: fmsLineState
fmsLineState.description: The value of this object is the state of this line.

fmsLineLcInUseCount.name: fmsLineLcInUseCount
fmsLineLcInUseCount.description: The value of this object is the total number of the busy logical channels.

fmsLineReinitsCounter.name: fmsLineReinitsCounter
fmsLineReinitsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the resets of this line from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsLineIncidentsCounter.name: fmsLineIncidentsCounter
fmsLineIncidentsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the incidents of this line from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsLineInputOctetsCounter.name: fmsLineInputOctetsCounter
fmsLineInputOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of the bytes received over this line from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsLineOutputOctetsCounter.name: fmsLineOutputOctetsCounter
fmsLineOutputOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the total number of bytes sent over this line from the beginning of the collection period.

fmsLineType.name: fmsLineType
fmsLineType.description: The value of this object indicates the type of this line.

fmsLineTestState.name: fmsLineTestState
fmsLineTestState.description: The value of this object indicates the test state of this line.

fmStatSignalTable.name: fmStatSignalTable
fmStatSignalTable.description: This table contains the information about the lines signals.

fmsSigPhysPortId.name: fmsSigPhysPortId
fmsSigPhysPortId.description: The value of this object is the one physical line identifier.

fmsSigState.name: fmsSigState
fmsSigState.description: The value of this object indictates the state of this line.

fmsSigDceOrDte.name: fmsSigDceOrDte
fmsSigDceOrDte.description: The value of this object indicates whether the equipment is DTE or DCE for this line.

fmsSig105.name: fmsSig105
fmsSig105.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 105 on this line.

fmsSig106.name: fmsSig106
fmsSig106.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 106 on this line.

fmsSig107.name: fmsSig107
fmsSig107.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 107 on this line.

fmsSig108.name: fmsSig108
fmsSig108.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 108 on this line.

fmsSig109.name: fmsSig109
fmsSig109.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 109 on this line.

fmsSig111.name: fmsSig111
fmsSig111.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 111 on this line.

fmsSig125.name: fmsSig125
fmsSig125.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 125 on this line.

fmsSig140.name: fmsSig140
fmsSig140.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 140 on this line.

fmsSig141.name: fmsSig141
fmsSig141.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 141 on this line.

fmsSig142.name: fmsSig142
fmsSig142.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal 142 on this line.

fmsSigSyn.name: fmsSigSyn
fmsSigSyn.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the signal SYN on this line.

fmsLinesSummState.name: fmsLinesSummState
fmsLinesSummState.description: This object indicates the state of each line of the equipment with the following format,. each line using three octets (i.e., 24 bits) : bit 0 : physical level (0 = down, 1 = up), bit 1: level 3 (0 = down, 1 = up), bits 2 to 8 : protocol (1 = X25 synchronous, 2 = asynchronous, 4 = asynchronous SDLC, 6 = asynchronous VIP character, 7 = BSC Transparent character, 8 = asynchronous on BSC 3270 or 2780/3780, 14 = ISDN D-Channel with or without PLL, 15 = ISDN B-Channel with signalling, 16 = ISDN B-Channel without signalling, 19 = Frame Relay transit or FR-TE, 20 = HDLC-T, 21 = Frame Relay subscriber, FRA, 23 = Ethernet, 30 = asynchronous X28+), bits 9 to 20 : number of active logical channels (0 to 4095), bits 20 to 23 : unused.

fmStatStateTable.name: fmStatStateTable
fmStatStateTable.description: This table contains the information about the type and the state of the lines.

fmsStateLine.name: fmsStateLine
fmsStateLine.description: The value of this object is the one line identifier.

fmsStateLineType.name: fmsStateLineType
fmsStateLineType.description: The value of this object indicates the type of this line.

fmsStateOsiState.name: fmsStateOsiState
fmsStateOsiState.description: The value of this object indicates the state and the ISO layer of this line. If this line is up, the value indicated is the ISO layer.

fmsStateTestState.name: fmsStateTestState
fmsStateTestState.description: The value of this object indicates the test state of this line.

fmsStateMlpTrunkMainLine.name: fmsStateMlpTrunkMainLine
fmsStateMlpTrunkMainLine.description: The value of this object indicates if this line is the main line of a MLP trunk.

fmsStateMlpTrunkNumber.name: fmsStateMlpTrunkNumber
fmsStateMlpTrunkNumber.description: The value of this object is the identifier of the MLP trunk.

fmsStateMlpTrunkState.name: fmsStateMlpTrunkState
fmsStateMlpTrunkState.description: The value of this object is the MLP trunk state.

fmStatMlpTable.name: fmStatMlpTable
fmStatMlpTable.description: This table contains the information about the MLP trunks.

fmsMlpTrunkNumber.name: fmsMlpTrunkNumber
fmsMlpTrunkNumber.description: The value of this object is the identifier of the MLP trunk.

fmsMlpLineId.name: fmsMlpLineId
fmsMlpLineId.description: The value of this object is the one line identifier.

fmsMlpLineType.name: fmsMlpLineType
fmsMlpLineType.description: The value of this object indicates if this line is the main line of this MLP trunk.

fmStatEthernetTable.name: fmStatEthernetTable
fmStatEthernetTable.description: This table contains the general information about the Ethernet physical ports.

fmsEthLineId.name: fmsEthLineId
fmsEthLineId.description: The value of this object is the identifier of one physical port.

fmsEthPhysAddr.name: fmsEthPhysAddr
fmsEthPhysAddr.description: The value of this object is the MAC address of the equipment.

fmsEthOperStatus.name: fmsEthOperStatus
fmsEthOperStatus.description: The value of this object is the state of the LAN function.

fmsEthInterface.name: fmsEthInterface
fmsEthInterface.description: The value of this object is the ethernet connector type.

fmsEthAutoPortSelection.name: fmsEthAutoPortSelection
fmsEthAutoPortSelection.description: The value of this object indicates whether the selection of the LAN port is automatic or not.

fmsEthPolarityCorrection.name: fmsEthPolarityCorrection
fmsEthPolarityCorrection.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the polarity spontaneous correction.

fmsEthPolarityInversion.name: fmsEthPolarityInversion
fmsEthPolarityInversion.description: The value of this object indicates if there is inversion of the polarity.

fmsEthLinkIntegrity.name: fmsEthLinkIntegrity
fmsEthLinkIntegrity.description: The value of this object indicates the state of the link integrity function.

fmsEthTestLoopback.name: fmsEthTestLoopback
fmsEthTestLoopback.description: The value of this object indicates if the loopback test is used.

fmsEthJabber.name: fmsEthJabber
fmsEthJabber.description: The value of this object is the state of the bus taking time control function (Jabber).

fmsEthTestMode.name: fmsEthTestMode
fmsEthTestMode.description: The value of this object is the mode of the test. The value 'continousSending' indicates that frames are sent continously during the test. The value 'standby' indicates that no frames are sent during the test.

fmsEthTdrState.name: fmsEthTdrState
fmsEthTdrState.description: The value of this object (Time Domain Reflectometry) indicates the problem type of the connectors system.

fmsEthTdrLoc.name: fmsEthTdrLoc
fmsEthTdrLoc.description: The value of this object (Time Domain Reflectometry) indicates the tracing of connectors system problem. The value '2047' is not significant.

fmsEthUpTime.name: fmsEthUpTime
fmsEthUpTime.description: The value of this object is the time elapsing since the last start-up of the LAN interface. When the equipment starts, the value of this object is 0.

fmStatEthInputTrafficTable.name: fmStatEthInputTrafficTable
fmStatEthInputTrafficTable.description: This table contains the information about the statistics, in reception, of a LAN line. The values of all this counters are not reseted by the command 'reset' of fmsCtrlCountersCommand.

fmsEthInLineId.name: fmsEthInLineId
fmsEthInLineId.description: The value of this object is the one line identifier.

fmsEthInOctetsCounter.name: fmsEthInOctetsCounter
fmsEthInOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the bytes received over this line.

fmsEthInPktsCounter.name: fmsEthInPktsCounter
fmsEthInPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received over this line.

fmsEthInNoErrCounter.name: fmsEthInNoErrCounter
fmsEthInNoErrCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with no error over this line.

fmsEthInUcastPktsCounter.name: fmsEthInUcastPktsCounter
fmsEthInUcastPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received over this line and correctly sent to the upper layer.

fmsEthInAlignmentErrorsCounter.name: fmsEthInAlignmentErrorsCounter
fmsEthInAlignmentErrorsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with an error of alignment (number of bits not multiple of 8) over this line.

fmsEthInFCSErrorsCounter.name: fmsEthInFCSErrorsCounter
fmsEthInFCSErrorsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with an error of CRC over this line.

fmsEthInPktsTooLongsCounter.name: fmsEthInPktsTooLongsCounter
fmsEthInPktsTooLongsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with a length too long over this line.

fmsEthInPktsTooShortsCounter.name: fmsEthInPktsTooShortsCounter
fmsEthInPktsTooShortsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with a length too short over this line.

fmsEthInErrOutOfResourcesCounter.name: fmsEthInErrOutOfResourcesCounter
fmsEthInErrOutOfResourcesCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with an error of resources too short over this line.

fmsEthInErrDmaOverrunCounter.name: fmsEthInErrDmaOverrunCounter
fmsEthInErrDmaOverrunCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with the error 'DMA overrun' (no reply when expected by the memory bus to a DMA cycle) over this line.

fmsEthInErrCollCounter.name: fmsEthInErrCollCounter
fmsEthInErrCollCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received with the error 'receive collision' (frames received but invalided because of a collision detection during the reception) over this line.

fmsEthInErrOverFlowCounter.name: fmsEthInErrOverFlowCounter
fmsEthInErrOverFlowCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received over this line and not sent to the upper layer because of the resources overflow.

fmStatEthOutputTrafficTable.name: fmStatEthOutputTrafficTable
fmStatEthOutputTrafficTable.description: This table contains the information about the statistics, in sending, of one LAN line. The values of all this counters are not reseted by the command 'reset' of fmsCtrlCountersCommand.

fmsEthOutLineId.name: fmsEthOutLineId
fmsEthOutLineId.description: The value of this object is the one line identifier.

fmsEthOutOctetsCounter.name: fmsEthOutOctetsCounter
fmsEthOutOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the bytes sent over this line.

fmsEthOutPktsCounter.name: fmsEthOutPktsCounter
fmsEthOutPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames sent over this line.

fmsEthOutNoErrCounter.name: fmsEthOutNoErrCounter
fmsEthOutNoErrCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames sent without error over this line.

fmsEthOutSingleCollisionFramesCounter.name: fmsEthOutSingleCollisionFramesCounter
fmsEthOutSingleCollisionFramesCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames sent after one collision over this line.

fmsEthOutMultipleCollisionFramesCounter.name: fmsEthOutMultipleCollisionFramesCounter
fmsEthOutMultipleCollisionFramesCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames sent after two collisions or more over this line.

fmsEthOutDeferredTransmissionsCounter.name: fmsEthOutDeferredTransmissionsCounter
fmsEthOutDeferredTransmissionsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames sent late over this line because the ethernet bus is busy.

fmsEthOutSQETestErrorsCounter.name: fmsEthOutSQETestErrorsCounter
fmsEthOutSQETestErrorsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames sent with error of no heartbeat over this line. The heartbeat function of the ethernet transmitter is used to indicate to the LAN driver the status of its collision detector. If following a transmission, the transmitter does not send the SQE signal of the heartbeat function to the equipment, then the frame is considered to be sent with 'no heartbeat' error.

fmsEthOutLateCollisionsCounter.name: fmsEthOutLateCollisionsCounter
fmsEthOutLateCollisionsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames not sent because of the error 'late collision' (collision detection after the end of the slot time) over this line.

fmsEthOutExcessiveCollisionsCounter.name: fmsEthOutExcessiveCollisionsCounter
fmsEthOutExcessiveCollisionsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames not sent because of the collisions detections at all the attempts over this line.

fmsEthOutCarrierSenseErrorsCounter.name: fmsEthOutCarrierSenseErrorsCounter
fmsEthOutCarrierSenseErrorsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames not sent because of the error 'no carrier sense' over this line.

fmsEthOutErrExcdDelayCounter.name: fmsEthOutErrExcdDelayCounter
fmsEthOutErrExcdDelayCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames not sent over this line because the bus is busy during a long time.

fmsEthOutErrCtsLossCounter.name: fmsEthOutErrCtsLossCounter
fmsEthOutErrCtsLossCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames not sent over this line because of the loss of the CTS (Clear To Send) signal.

fmsEthOutErrDmaUnderrunCounter.name: fmsEthOutErrDmaUnderrunCounter
fmsEthOutErrDmaUnderrunCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames not sent over this line because of the error 'DMA underrun' (no reply when expected by the memory bus to a DMA cycle).

fmStatEthManagementTable.name: fmStatEthManagementTable
fmStatEthManagementTable.description: This table contains the information about the monitoring, the reset and the filtering for each port. The values of all this counters are not reseted by the command 'reset' of fmsCtrlCountersCommand.

fmsEthManLineId.name: fmsEthManLineId
fmsEthManLineId.description: The value of this object is the one line identifier.

fmsEthManSupervisionOkCounter.name: fmsEthManSupervisionOkCounter
fmsEthManSupervisionOkCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the OK supervision frames over this line.

fmsEthManSupervisionNokCounter.name: fmsEthManSupervisionNokCounter

fmsEthManInputResetCounter.name: fmsEthManInputResetCounter

fmsEthManFilterPermitCounter.name: fmsEthManFilterPermitCounter

fmsEthManFilterDenyCounter.name: fmsEthManFilterDenyCounter
fmsEthManFilterDenyCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames refused by the bridge filtering over this line.

fmsWanConnRemoteAddr.name: fmsWanConnRemoteAddr

fmsWanConnEncapsulation.name: fmsWanConnEncapsulation

fmsWanConnStatus.name: fmsWanConnStatus

fmsWanConnLocalSbNumber.name: fmsWanConnLocalSbNumber

fmsWanConnInPktsCounter.name: fmsWanConnInPktsCounter

fmsWanConnInErrPktsCounter.name: fmsWanConnInErrPktsCounter
fmsWanConnInErrPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of frames lost because they are erroneous over this SLL (Switched Logical Link).

fmsWanConnInOctetsCounter.name: fmsWanConnInOctetsCounter
fmsWanConnInOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of bytes received over this SLL (Switched Logical Link).

fmsWanConnOutPktsCounter.name: fmsWanConnOutPktsCounter

fmsWanConnOutOctetsCounter.name: fmsWanConnOutOctetsCounter
fmsWanConnOutOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of bytes sent over this SLL (Switched Logical Link).

fmsRvpConnRemoteAddr.name: fmsRvpConnRemoteAddr
fmsRvpConnRemoteAddr.description: The value of this object is the X121 address of the remote equipment.

fmsRvpConnEncapsulation.name: fmsRvpConnEncapsulation
fmsRvpConnEncapsulation.description: The value of this object indicates the encapsulation type.

fmsRvpConnId.name: fmsRvpConnId
fmsRvpConnId.description: The value of this object is the one connection identifier.

fmsRvpConnStatus.name: fmsRvpConnStatus

fmsRvpConnGrouping.name: fmsRvpConnGrouping
