fmsRvpConnLocalSbNumber.name: fmsRvpConnLocalSbNumber
fmsRvpConnLocalSbNumber.description: The value of this object is the subscriber local number AB (in the DNIC ZO AB plan) of this connection.

fmsRvpConnInPktsCounter.name: fmsRvpConnInPktsCounter
fmsRvpConnInPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of frames received over this connection.

fmsRvpConnInErrPktsCounter.name: fmsRvpConnInErrPktsCounter
fmsRvpConnInErrPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of frames lost because they are erroneous over this connection.

fmsRvpConnInOctetsCounter.name: fmsRvpConnInOctetsCounter
fmsRvpConnInOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of bytes received over this connection.

fmsRvpConnOutPktsCounter.name: fmsRvpConnOutPktsCounter
fmsRvpConnOutPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of frames sent over this connection.

fmsRvpConnOutOctetsCounter.name: fmsRvpConnOutOctetsCounter
fmsRvpConnOutOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of bytes sent over this connection.

fmsBridgeState.name: fmsBridgeState
fmsBridgeState.description: The value of this object is the state of the bridging function.

fmsBrdgTrafInPktsCounter.name: fmsBrdgTrafInPktsCounter
fmsBrdgTrafInPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames received by the bridge.

fmsBrdgTrafOutPktsCounter.name: fmsBrdgTrafOutPktsCounter
fmsBrdgTrafOutPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the frames sent by the bridge.

fmsBrdgTrafOutBroadcastPktsCounter.name: fmsBrdgTrafOutBroadcastPktsCounter
fmsBrdgTrafOutBroadcastPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the data frames diffusions.

fmsBrdgTrafInServCounter.name: fmsBrdgTrafInServCounter
fmsBrdgTrafInServCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the RIL service frames received by the bridge.

fmsBrdgTrafOutServCounter.name: fmsBrdgTrafOutServCounter
fmsBrdgTrafOutServCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the RIL service frames sent by the bridge.

fmsBrdgTrafOutBroadcastServCounter.name: fmsBrdgTrafOutBroadcastServCounter
fmsBrdgTrafOutBroadcastServCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the service frames diffusions.

fmsIpRouterState.name: fmsIpRouterState
fmsIpRouterState.description: The value of this object is the state of the IP routing function.

fmsIpTrafInReceivesCounter.name: fmsIpTrafInReceivesCounter
fmsIpTrafInReceivesCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received.

fmsIpTrafOutRequestsCounter.name: fmsIpTrafOutRequestsCounter
fmsIpTrafOutRequestsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams sent.

fmsIpTrafInOctetsCounter.name: fmsIpTrafInOctetsCounter
fmsIpTrafInOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the bytes received with the IP protocol.

fmsIpTrafOutOctetsCounter.name: fmsIpTrafOutOctetsCounter
fmsIpTrafOutOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the bytes sent with the IP protocol.

fmsIpTrafInUnknownProtosCounter.name: fmsIpTrafInUnknownProtosCounter
fmsIpTrafInUnknownProtosCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received and lost because of an unknown protocol.

fmsIpTrafNoRoutesCounter.name: fmsIpTrafNoRoutesCounter
fmsIpTrafNoRoutesCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received and lost because of an impossible routing.

fmsIpTrafInHdrErrorsCounter.name: fmsIpTrafInHdrErrorsCounter
fmsIpTrafInHdrErrorsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received and lost because they are erroneous.

fmsIpTrafOutForwDatagramsCounter.name: fmsIpTrafOutForwDatagramsCounter
fmsIpTrafOutForwDatagramsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received and correctly routed.

fmsIpTrafOutForwDefRouteCounter.name: fmsIpTrafOutForwDefRouteCounter
fmsIpTrafOutForwDefRouteCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received and routed on the default route.

fmsIpTrafIcmpOutMsgsCounter.name: fmsIpTrafIcmpOutMsgsCounter
fmsIpTrafIcmpOutMsgsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the ICMP datagrams sent.

fmsIpTrafIcmpInMsgsCounter.name: fmsIpTrafIcmpInMsgsCounter
fmsIpTrafIcmpInMsgsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the ICMP datagrams received.

fmsIpLanIpAddr.name: fmsIpLanIpAddr
fmsIpLanIpAddr.description: fmStatIpLanTraffic 0 The value of this object is the IP address of the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanNetMask.name: fmsIpLanNetMask
fmsIpLanNetMask.description: The value of this object is the sub-network mask of the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanOutRequestsCounter.name: fmsIpLanOutRequestsCounter
fmsIpLanOutRequestsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams sent on the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanInReceivesCounter.name: fmsIpLanInReceivesCounter
fmsIpLanInReceivesCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received on the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanOutOctetsIpCounter.name: fmsIpLanOutOctetsIpCounter
fmsIpLanOutOctetsIpCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the bytes sent with the IP protocol on the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanInOctetsIpCounter.name: fmsIpLanInOctetsIpCounter
fmsIpLanInOctetsIpCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the bytes received with the IP protocol on the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanNoRoutesCounter.name: fmsIpLanNoRoutesCounter
fmsIpLanNoRoutesCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received and lost because of impossible routing, on the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanInHdrErrorsCounter.name: fmsIpLanInHdrErrorsCounter
fmsIpLanInHdrErrorsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the IP datagrams received and lost because of they are erroneous, on the LAN interface.

fmsIpLanArpFailedCounter.name: fmsIpLanArpFailedCounter
fmsIpLanArpFailedCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of the not solved ARP request, on the LAN interface.

fmsFrSwDataLinkConnEstablished.name: fmsFrSwDataLinkConnEstablished
fmsFrSwDataLinkConnEstablished.description: Nb de connexions FR etablis (svc-svc, pvc-svc, proto-svc).

fmsFrSwBookingInputThrouhput.name: fmsFrSwBookingInputThrouhput
fmsFrSwBookingInputThrouhput.description: Debit reserve (somme des CIR abonnes vers reseau).

fmsFrSwOverBookingThrouhput.name: fmsFrSwOverBookingThrouhput
fmsFrSwOverBookingThrouhput.description: Debit reserve par les SVC en surbooking.

fmsFrLpNumPlan.name: fmsFrLpNumPlan
fmsFrLpNumPlan.description: The value of this object identifies the network address numbering plan for this logical port. The network address is the object ifPhysAddress. The value none implies that there is no ifPhysAddress. The SNMP agent will return an octet string of zero length for ifPhysAddress. The value other means that an address has been assigned to this interface, but the numbering plan is not enumerated here.

fmsFrLpAddrDlciLen.name: fmsFrLpAddrDlciLen
fmsFrLpAddrDlciLen.description: The value of this object identifies the Q.922 Address field length and DLCI length for this logical port.

fmsFrLpVcSigProtocol.name: fmsFrLpVcSigProtocol
fmsFrLpVcSigProtocol.description: The value of this object identifies the Local In-Channel Signaling Protocol that is used for this frame relay logical port.

fmsFrLpInOctets.name: fmsFrLpInOctets
fmsFrLpInOctets.description: The number of received octets. This counter only counts octets from the beginning of the frame relay header field to the end of user data.

fmsFrLpInFrames.name: fmsFrLpInFrames
fmsFrLpInFrames.description: The number of received unerrored, unicast frames.

fmsFrLpInErrors.name: fmsFrLpInErrors
fmsFrLpInErrors.description: The number of received frames that are discarded, because of an error. Possible errors can be the following: the frame relay frames were too long or were too short.

fmsFrLpInFrHeaderErrors.name: fmsFrLpInFrHeaderErrors
fmsFrLpInFrHeaderErrors.description: The number of received frames that are discarded, because of an error. Possible errors can be the following: the frames had an invalid or unrecognized DLCI values, or incorrect header values.

fmsFrLpInFecnFrames.name: fmsFrLpInFecnFrames
fmsFrLpInFecnFrames.description: Number of frames received indicating forward congestion.

fmsFrLpInBecnFrames.name: fmsFrLpInBecnFrames
fmsFrLpInBecnFrames.description: Number of frames received indicating backward congestion.

fmsFrLpInExcessFrames.name: fmsFrLpInExcessFrames
fmsFrLpInExcessFrames.description: Only on FR-CE or FR-TE logical ports : The number of frames received by the equipment (ingress) for this logical port which were treated as excess traffic. Frames which are sent to the equipment with DE set to zero are treated as excess when more than Bc bits are submitted to the equipment during the Committed Information Rate Measurement Interval (Tc). Excess traffic may or may not be discarded at the ingress if more than Bc + Be bits are submitted to the equipment during Tc. Traffic discarded at the ingress is not recorded in this object. Frames which are sent to the equipement with DE set to one are also treated as excess traffic.

fmsFrLpInDiscards.name: fmsFrLpInDiscards
fmsFrLpInDiscards.description: Only on FR-CE or FR-TE logical ports : The number of frames received by the equipment (ingress) that were discarded due to traffic enforcement for this logical port.

fmsFrLpOutOctets.name: fmsFrLpOutOctets
fmsFrLpOutOctets.description: The number of transmitted octets. This counter only counts octets from the beginning of the frame relay header field to the end of user data.

fmsFrLpOutFecnFrames.name: fmsFrLpOutFecnFrames
fmsFrLpOutFecnFrames.description: Number of frames sent indicating forward congestion.

fmsFrLpOutLocalCongFecnFrames.name: fmsFrLpOutLocalCongFecnFrames
fmsFrLpOutLocalCongFecnFrames.description: Number of frames sent indicating forward congestion due to traffic enforcement on this logical port.

fmsFrLpOutBecnFrames.name: fmsFrLpOutBecnFrames
fmsFrLpOutBecnFrames.description: Number of frames sent indicating backward congestion.

fmsFrLpOutLocalCongBecnFrames.name: fmsFrLpOutLocalCongBecnFrames
fmsFrLpOutLocalCongBecnFrames.description: Number of frames sent indicating backward congestion due to traffic enforcement on the incoming logical port.

fmsFrLpOutLocalCongDiscards.name: fmsFrLpOutLocalCongDiscards
fmsFrLpOutLocalCongDiscards.description: The number of frames not sent by the equipment (egress) due to traffic enforcement on this logical port.

fmsFrLpLmiProced.name: fmsFrLpLmiProced
fmsFrLpLmiProced.description: The value of this object identifies the Local In-Channel Signaling Procedure that is used for this logical port. The logical port can be performing user-to-network network-side procedures, bidirectional procedures or user-to-network user-side procedures.

fmsFrLpLmiUserN391.name: fmsFrLpLmiUserN391
fmsFrLpLmiUserN391.description: The value of this object identifies the User-side N391 full status polling cycle value for this logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is not significant. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A and T1.617 Annex D.

fmsFrLpLmiUserN392.name: fmsFrLpLmiUserN392
fmsFrLpLmiUserN392.description: The value of this object identifies the User-side N392 error threshold value for this logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is not significant. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A and T1.617 Annex D.

fmsFrLpLmiUserN393.name: fmsFrLpLmiUserN393
fmsFrLpLmiUserN393.description: The value of this object identifies the User-side N393 monitored events count value for this logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is not significant. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A and T1.617 Annex D.

fmsFrLpLmiUserT391.name: fmsFrLpLmiUserT391
fmsFrLpLmiUserT391.description: The value of this object identifies the User-side T391 link integrity verification polling timer value for this logical port. If the logical port is not performing user-side procedures, then this value is not significant. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A and T1.617 Annex D.

fmsFrLpLmiNetN392.name: fmsFrLpLmiNetN392
fmsFrLpLmiNetN392.description: The value of this object identifies the Network-side N392 error threshold value (nN2 for LMI) for this logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is not significant. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A, T1.617 Annex D and LMI.

fmsFrLpLmiNetN393.name: fmsFrLpLmiNetN393
fmsFrLpLmiNetN393.description: The value of this object identifies the Network-side N393 monitored events count value (nN3 for LMI) for this logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is not significant. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A, T1.617 Annex D and LMI.

fmsFrLpLmiNetT392.name: fmsFrLpLmiNetT392
fmsFrLpLmiNetT392.description: The value of this object identifies the Network-side T392 polling verification timer value (nT2 for LMI) for this logical port. If the logical port is not performing network-side procedures, then this value is not significant. This object applies to Q.933 Annex A, T1.617 Annex D and LMI.

fmsFrLpSvcDlcInitialized.name: fmsFrLpSvcDlcInitialized
fmsFrLpSvcDlcInitialized.description: Nb de Data Link Connexion correctement initialises.

fmsFrDlcState.name: fmsFrDlcState
fmsFrDlcState.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual circuit is operational.

fmsFrDlcInDlci.name: fmsFrDlcInDlci
fmsFrDlcInDlci.description: The value of this object is equal to the DLCI value for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcInFrames.name: fmsFrDlcInFrames
fmsFrDlcInFrames.description: The number of frames received by the equipment (ingress) for this Data Link Connection. This includes any frames discarded by the equipment due to submitting more than Bc + Be data or due to any network congestion recovery procedure.

fmsFrDlcInOctets.name: fmsFrDlcInOctets
fmsFrDlcInOctets.description: The number of octets received by the equipment (ingress) for this Data Link Connection. This counter only counts octets from the beginning of the frame relay header field to the end of user data.

fmsFrDlcInDeFrames.name: fmsFrDlcInDeFrames
fmsFrDlcInDeFrames.description: The number of frames received by the equipment (ingress) with the DE bit set to (1) for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcInFecnFrames.name: fmsFrDlcInFecnFrames
fmsFrDlcInFecnFrames.description: Number of frames received by the equipment indicating forward congestion for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcInBecnFrames.name: fmsFrDlcInBecnFrames
fmsFrDlcInBecnFrames.description: Number of frames received by the equipment indicating backward congestion for this Data Link Connection

fmsFrDlcInExcessFrames.name: fmsFrDlcInExcessFrames
fmsFrDlcInExcessFrames.description: The number of frames received by the equipment (ingress) for this Data Link Connection which were treated as excess traffic. Frames which are sent to the equipment with DE set to zero are treated as excess when more than Bc bits are submitted to the network during the Committed Information Rate Measurement Interval (Tc). Excess traffic may or may not be discarded at the ingress if more than Bc + Be bits are submitted to the equipment during Tc. Traffic discarded at the ingress is not recorded in this object. Frames which are sent to the equipment with DE set to one are also treated as excess traffic.

fmsFrDlcInDiscards.name: fmsFrDlcInDiscards
fmsFrDlcInDiscards.description: The number of frames received by the equipment (ingress) that were discarded due to traffic enforcement for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcInLostFrames.name: fmsFrDlcInLostFrames
fmsFrDlcInLostFrames.description: Nb de trames perdues dans le reseau (evalue par le mecanisme de segmentation / reassemblage).

fmsFrDlcInLostSegments.name: fmsFrDlcInLostSegments
fmsFrDlcInLostSegments.description: Nb de segments perdus dans le reseau (evalue par le mecanisme de segmentation / reassemblage).

fmsFrDlcOutDlci.name: fmsFrDlcOutDlci
fmsFrDlcOutDlci.description: The value of this object is equal to the DLCI value for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcOutFrames.name: fmsFrDlcOutFrames
fmsFrDlcOutFrames.description: The number of frames sent by the equipment (egress) regardless of whether they are Bc or Be frames for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcOutOctets.name: fmsFrDlcOutOctets
fmsFrDlcOutOctets.description: The number of octets sent by the equipment (egress) for this Data Link Connection. This counter only counts octets from the beginning of the frame relay header field to the end of user data.

fmsFrDlcOutFecnFrames.name: fmsFrDlcOutFecnFrames
fmsFrDlcOutFecnFrames.description: Number of frames sent by the equipment indicating forward congestion for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcOutBecnFrames.name: fmsFrDlcOutBecnFrames
fmsFrDlcOutBecnFrames.description: Number of frames sent by the equipment indicating backward congestion for this Data Link Connection.

fmsFrDlcOutExcessFrames.name: fmsFrDlcOutExcessFrames
fmsFrDlcOutExcessFrames.description: The number of frames sent by the equipment (egress) for this Data Link Connection which were treated as excess traffic. (The DE bit may be set to one.).

fmsFrDlcOutDiscards.name: fmsFrDlcOutDiscards
fmsFrDlcOutDiscards.description: Number of frames not sent by the equipment due to congestion for this Data Link Connection.

fmStatFrLineTable.name: fmStatFrLineTable
fmStatFrLineTable.description: This table contains the information about the Frame Relay lines.

fmsFrLineId.name: fmsFrLineId
fmsFrLineId.description: The value of this object is the one physical line identifier.

fmsFrLineStatus.name: fmsFrLineStatus
fmsFrLineStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the state of this physical line.

fmsFrLineLmiStatus.name: fmsFrLineLmiStatus
fmsFrLineLmiStatus.description: The value of this object indicates the LMI state.

fmsFrLineCircuitCount.name: fmsFrLineCircuitCount
fmsFrLineCircuitCount.description: The value of this object indicates the total number of the DLCI on this physical line.

fmsFrLineActiveCircuitCount.name: fmsFrLineActiveCircuitCount
fmsFrLineActiveCircuitCount.description: The value of this objects is the number of active DLCI on this physical line.

fmStatFrCircuitTable.name: fmStatFrCircuitTable
fmStatFrCircuitTable.description: This table contains the information about each circuit.

fmsFrCircuitLineId.name: fmsFrCircuitLineId
fmsFrCircuitLineId.description: The value of this object is the one physical line identifier.

fmsFrCircuitDlci.name: fmsFrCircuitDlci
fmsFrCircuitDlci.description: The value of this object is the identifier of one circuit. It is the DLCI.

fmsFrCircuitStatus.name: fmsFrCircuitStatus
fmsFrCircuitStatus.description: The value of this object is the state of this circuit.

fmsFrCircuitAge.name: fmsFrCircuitAge
fmsFrCircuitAge.description: The value of this object indicates the age of this circuit.

fmsFrCircuitOutOctetsCounter.name: fmsFrCircuitOutOctetsCounter
fmsFrCircuitOutOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of octets sent on this circuit.

fmsFrCircuitInOctetsCounter.name: fmsFrCircuitInOctetsCounter
fmsFrCircuitInOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of octets received on this circuit.

fmStatPppPhysLineTable.name: fmStatPppPhysLineTable
fmStatPppPhysLineTable.description: This table contains the general information about PPP lines.

fmsPppPhysLineId.name: fmsPppPhysLineId
fmsPppPhysLineId.description: The value of this object is the one physical port identifier.

fmsPppPhysLocalMru.name: fmsPppPhysLocalMru
fmsPppPhysLocalMru.description: The value of this object is the current value of the MRU (Maximum Receive Unit) for the local PPP entity. This value is the MRU that the remote entity is using when sending packets to the local PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

fmsPppPhysRemoteMru.name: fmsPppPhysRemoteMru
fmsPppPhysRemoteMru.description: The value of this object is the current value of the MRU (Maximum Receive Unit) for the remote PPP entity. This value is the MRU that the local entity is using when sending packets to the remote PPP entity. The value of this object is meaningful only when the link has reached the open state (ifOperStatus is up).

fmsPppPhysMagicNumber.name: fmsPppPhysMagicNumber
fmsPppPhysMagicNumber.description: The value of this object indicates the magic number state. If 'used' then the local node will attempt to perform Magic Number negotiation with the remote node. If 'notUsed' then this negotiation is not performed. In any event, the local node will comply with any magic number negotiations attempted by the remote node, per the PPP specification. Changing this object will have an effect when the link is next restarted.

fmStatPppProtocolStatusTable.name: fmStatPppProtocolStatusTable
fmStatPppProtocolStatusTable.description: This table contains the information about the protocol layers (LCP and NCP level) for each PPP line.

fmsPppProtoLineId.name: fmsPppProtoLineId
fmsPppProtoLineId.description: The value of this object is the one PPP line identifier.

fmsPppProtoLcpStatus.name: fmsPppProtoLcpStatus
fmsPppProtoLcpStatus.description: The value of this object is the current state of the LCP layer.

fmsPppProtoLcpDiag.name: fmsPppProtoLcpDiag
fmsPppProtoLcpDiag.description: The value of this object is the LCP layer diagnostic report.

fmsPppProtoIpNcpStatus.name: fmsPppProtoIpNcpStatus
fmsPppProtoIpNcpStatus.description: The value of this object is the current state of the IP NCP layer.

fmsPppProtoIpNcpDiag.name: fmsPppProtoIpNcpDiag
fmsPppProtoIpNcpDiag.description: The value of this object is the IP NCP layer diagnostic report.

fmsPppProtoBrdgNcpStatus.name: fmsPppProtoBrdgNcpStatus
fmsPppProtoBrdgNcpStatus.description: The value of this object is the current state of the Bridge NCP layer.

fmsPppProtoBrdgNcpDiag.name: fmsPppProtoBrdgNcpDiag
fmsPppProtoBrdgNcpDiag.description: The value of this object is the Bridge NCP layer diagnostic report.

fmsPppProtoIpxNcpStatus.name: fmsPppProtoIpxNcpStatus
fmsPppProtoIpxNcpStatus.description: The value of this object is the current state of the IPX NCP layer.

fmsPppProtoIpxNcpDiag.name: fmsPppProtoIpxNcpDiag
fmsPppProtoIpxNcpDiag.description: The value of this object is the IPX NCP layer diagnostic report.

fmsPppProtoClnpNcpStatus.name: fmsPppProtoClnpNcpStatus
fmsPppProtoClnpNcpStatus.description: The value of this object is the current state of the CLNP NCP layer.

fmsPppProtoClnpNcpDiag.name: fmsPppProtoClnpNcpDiag
fmsPppProtoClnpNcpDiag.description: The value of this object is the CLNP NCP layer diagnostic report.

fmsE1Ds1ChIfNumber.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfNumber
fmsE1Ds1ChIfNumber.description: Nombre de canaux E1 ou DS1

fmsE1Ds1ChIfLastChange.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfLastChange
fmsE1Ds1ChIfLastChange.description: Valeur de sysUpTime au moment ou l'interface est passe dans l'etat operationnel courant

fmsE1Ds1ChIfInNUcastPkts.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfInNUcastPkts
fmsE1Ds1ChIfInNUcastPkts.description: Nombre de paquets non Unicast recus

fmsE1Ds1ChIfInErrors.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfInErrors
fmsE1Ds1ChIfInErrors.description: Nombre de paquets recus en erreur

fmsE1Ds1ChIfInUnknownProtos.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfInUnknownProtos
fmsE1Ds1ChIfInUnknownProtos.description: Nombre de paquets recus avec protocole inconnu

fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutNUcastPkts.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutNUcastPkts
fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutNUcastPkts.description: Nombre de paquets non Unicast emis

fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutErrors.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutErrors
fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutErrors.description: Nombre de paquets emis en erreur

fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutQLen.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutQLen
fmsE1Ds1ChIfOutQLen.description: Longueur de la file des paquets emis

fmsE1Ds1ChIfSpecific.name: fmsE1Ds1ChIfSpecific
fmsE1Ds1ChIfSpecific.description: OID de la MIB de reference

fmsS2BChIfLastChange.name: fmsS2BChIfLastChange
fmsS2BChIfLastChange.description: Valeur de sysUpTime au moment ou le canal est passe dans l'etat operationnel courant

fmsS0BChPhysIfId.name: fmsS0BChPhysIfId
fmsS0BChPhysIfId.description: The value of this object is the number of the physical port the basic rate interface B channel is related to.

fmsS0BChChannelId.name: fmsS0BChChannelId
fmsS0BChChannelId.description: The value of this object is the identification number of the basic rate interface B channel.

fmsS0BChProto.name: fmsS0BChProto
fmsS0BChProto.description: The value of this object is the protocol related to the basic rate interface B channel.

fmsS0BChIfSpeed.name: fmsS0BChIfSpeed
fmsS0BChIfSpeed.description: The value of this object is the speed of the basic rate interface B channel.

fmsS0BChAdminStatus.name: fmsS0BChAdminStatus
fmsS0BChAdminStatus.description: The value of this object is the operational state wanted for the basic rate interface B channel.

fmsS0BChOperStatus.name: fmsS0BChOperStatus
fmsS0BChOperStatus.description: The value of this object is the current operational state of the basic rate interface B channel.

fmsS0BChIfLastChange.name: fmsS0BChIfLastChange
fmsS0BChIfLastChange.description: The value of this object is the value of the sysUpTime at the time when the basic rate interface B channel took its current operational state.

fmsS0BChIfInOctets.name: fmsS0BChIfInOctets
fmsS0BChIfInOctets.description: The value of this object is the number of bytes received on the basic rate interface B channel.

fmsS0BChIfOutOctets.name: fmsS0BChIfOutOctets
fmsS0BChIfOutOctets.description: The value of this object is the number of bytes sent on the basic rate interface B channel.

fmsS0BChIfCalledAddress.name: fmsS0BChIfCalledAddress
fmsS0BChIfCalledAddress.description: The value of this object is the called address.

fmsS0BChIfCallingAddress.name: fmsS0BChIfCallingAddress
fmsS0BChIfCallingAddress.description: The value of this object is the caller address.

fmRip2GlobalRouteChanges.name: fmRip2GlobalRouteChanges
fmRip2GlobalRouteChanges.description: RIP2 Global Route Changes. The number of changes made to the IP Route Database by RIP.

fmRip2GlobalQueries.name: fmRip2GlobalQueries
fmRip2GlobalQueries.description: RIP2 Global Queries. The number of responses sent to RIP queries from other systems.

fmRip2IfStatTable.name: fmRip2IfStatTable
fmRip2IfStatTable.description: A list of subnets which require separate status monitoring in RIP

fmRip2IfStatAddress.name: fmRip2IfStatAddress
fmRip2IfStatAddress.description: RIP2 Interface Stat Ip Address. The IP Address of this system on the indicated subnet

fmRip2IfStatRcvBadPackets.name: fmRip2IfStatRcvBadPackets
fmRip2IfStatRcvBadPackets.description: RIP2 Interface Stat Received Bad Packets. The number of RIP response packets received bythe RIP process which were subsequently discarded for any reason (e.g. a version 0 packet, or an unknown command type).

fmRip2IfStatRcvBadRoutes.name: fmRip2IfStatRcvBadRoutes
fmRip2IfStatRcvBadRoutes.description: RIP2 Interface Stat Received Bad Routes. The number of routes, in valid RIP packets,which were ignored for any reason (e.g. unknown address family, or invalid metric).

fmRip2IfStatSentUpdates.name: fmRip2IfStatSentUpdates
fmRip2IfStatSentUpdates.description: RIP2 Interface Stat Sent Updates. The number of triggered RIP updates actually sent on this interface. This explicitly does NOT include full updates sent containing new information.

fmRip2IfStatStatus.name: fmRip2IfStatStatus
fmRip2IfStatStatus.description: RIP2 Interface Stat Status. Writing invalid has the effect of deleting this interface.

fmRip2IfConfTable.name: fmRip2IfConfTable
fmRip2IfConfTable.description: A list of subnets which require separate configuration in RIP.

fmRip2IfConfAddress.name: fmRip2IfConfAddress
fmRip2IfConfAddress.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Ip Address. The IP Address of this system on the indicated subnet.

fmRip2IfConfDomain.name: fmRip2IfConfDomain
fmRip2IfConfDomain.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Domain. Value inserted into the Routing Domain field of all RIP packets sent on this interface.

fmRip2IfConfAuthType.name: fmRip2IfConfAuthType
fmRip2IfConfAuthType.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Authentiction Type. The type of Authentication used on this interface.

fmRip2IfConfAuthKey.name: fmRip2IfConfAuthKey
fmRip2IfConfAuthKey.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Authentication Key. The value to be used as the Authentication Key whenever the corresponding instance of rip2IfConfAuthType has the value simplePassword. A modification of the corresponding instance of rip2IfConfAuthType does not modify the rip2IfConfAuthKey value. If a string shorter than 16 octets is supplied, it will be left-justified and padded to 16 octets, on the right, with nulls (0x00). Reading this object always results in an OCTET STRING of length zero; authentication may not be bypassed by reading the MIB object.

fmRip2IfConfSend.name: fmRip2IfConfSend
fmRip2IfConfSend.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Send. What the router sends on this interface. ripVersion1 implies sending RIP updates compliant with RFC 1058. rip1Compatible implies broadcasting RIP-2 updates using RFC 1058 route subsumption rules. ripVersion2 implies multicasting RIP-2 updates.

fmRip2IfConfReceive.name: fmRip2IfConfReceive
fmRip2IfConfReceive.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Receive. This indicates which version of RIP updates are to be accepted. Note that rip2 and rip1OrRip2 implies reception of multicast packets.

fmRip2IfConfDefaultMetric.name: fmRip2IfConfDefaultMetric
fmRip2IfConfDefaultMetric.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Default Metric. This variable indicates what metric is to be used as a default route in RIP updates originated on this interface. A value of zero indicates that no default route should be originated; in this case, a default route via another router may be propagated.

fmRip2IfConfStatus.name: fmRip2IfConfStatus
fmRip2IfConfStatus.description: RIP2 Interface Conf Status. Writing invalid has the effect of deleting this interface.

fmRip2PeerAddress.name: fmRip2PeerAddress
fmRip2PeerAddress.description: RIP2 Peer Ip Address. The IP Address of the Peer System.

fmRip2PeerDomain.name: fmRip2PeerDomain
fmRip2PeerDomain.description: RIP2 Peer Domain. The value in the Routing Domain field in RIP packets received from the peer

fmRip2PeerLastUpdate.name: fmRip2PeerLastUpdate
fmRip2PeerLastUpdate.description: RIP2 Peer Last Update. The value of sysUpTime when the most recent RIP update was received from this system.

fmRip2PeerVersion.name: fmRip2PeerVersion
fmRip2PeerVersion.description: RIP2 Peer Version. The RIP version number in the header of the last RIP packet received.

fmRip2PeerRcvBadPackets.name: fmRip2PeerRcvBadPackets
fmRip2PeerRcvBadPackets.description: RIP2 Peer Received Bad Packets. The number of RIP response packets from this peer discarded as invalid.

fmRip2PeerRcvBadRoutes.name: fmRip2PeerRcvBadRoutes
fmRip2PeerRcvBadRoutes.description: RIP2 Peer Received Bad Routes. The number of routes from this peer that were ignored because the entry format was invalid.

fmOspfStandardRouterId.name: fmOspfStandardRouterId
fmOspfStandardRouterId.description: OSPF Router Id. A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the router in the Autonomous System. By convention, to ensure uniqueness, this should default to the value of one of the router's IP interface addresses.

fmOspfStandardAdminStat.name: fmOspfStandardAdminStat
fmOspfStandardAdminStat.description: OSPF Administrative Status. The administrative status of OSPF in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPF Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces.

fmOspfStandardVersionNumber.name: fmOspfStandardVersionNumber
fmOspfStandardVersionNumber.description: OSPF Version Number. The current version number of the OSPF protocol is 2.

fmOspfStandardAreaBdrRtrStatus.name: fmOspfStandardAreaBdrRtrStatus
fmOspfStandardAreaBdrRtrStatus.description: OSPF Area Border Router Status. A flag to note whether this router is an area border router.

fmOspfStandardASBdrRtrStatus.name: fmOspfStandardASBdrRtrStatus
fmOspfStandardASBdrRtrStatus.description: OSPF AS Border Router Status A flag to note whether this router is an Autonomous System border router.

fmOspfStandardExternLSACount.name: fmOspfStandardExternLSACount
fmOspfStandardExternLSACount.description: OSPF Extern LSA Count. The number of external (LS type 5) link-state advertisements in the link-state database.

fmOspfStandardExternLSACksumSum.name: fmOspfStandardExternLSACksumSum
fmOspfStandardExternLSACksumSum.description: OSPF Extern LSA Checksum. The 32-bit unsigned sum of the LS checksums of the external link-state advertisements contained in the link-state database. This sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.

fmOspfStandardTOSSupport.name: fmOspfStandardTOSSupport
fmOspfStandardTOSSupport.description: OSPF TOS Support. The router's support for type-of-service routing.

fmOspfStandardOriginateNewLSAs.name: fmOspfStandardOriginateNewLSAs
fmOspfStandardOriginateNewLSAs.description: OSPF Originate New LSAs. The number of new link-state advertisements that have been originated. This number is incremented each time the router originates a new LSA.

fmOspfStandardRxNewLSAs.name: fmOspfStandardRxNewLSAs
fmOspfStandardRxNewLSAs.description: OSPF Receive New LSAs. The number of link-state advertisements received determined to be new instantiations. This number does not include newer instantiations of self-originated link-state advertisements.

fmOspfStandardAreaTable.name: fmOspfStandardAreaTable
fmOspfStandardAreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas.

fmOspfStandardAreaId.name: fmOspfStandardAreaId
fmOspfStandardAreaId.description: OSPF Area Id. A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

fmOspfStandardAuthType.name: fmOspfStandardAuthType
fmOspfStandardAuthType.description: OSPF Area Authentication Type. The authentication type specified for an area. Additional authentication types may be assigned locally on a per Area basis.

fmOspfStandardImportASExtern.name: fmOspfStandardImportASExtern
fmOspfStandardImportASExtern.description: OSPF Area Import AS Extern. The area's support for importing AS external link-state advertisements.

fmOspfStandardSpfRuns.name: fmOspfStandardSpfRuns
fmOspfStandardSpfRuns.description: OSPF Area SPF Runs. The number of times that the intra-area route table has been calculated using this area's link-state database. This is typically done using Dijkstra's algorithm.

fmOspfStandardAreaBdrRtrCount.name: fmOspfStandardAreaBdrRtrCount
fmOspfStandardAreaBdrRtrCount.description: OSPF Area Border Router Count. The total number of area border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.

fmOspfStandardASBdrRtrCount.name: fmOspfStandardASBdrRtrCount
fmOspfStandardASBdrRtrCount.description: OSPF Area AS Border Router Count. The total number of Autonomous System border routers reachable within this area. This is initially zero, and is calculated in each SPF Pass.

fmOspfStandardAreaLSACount.name: fmOspfStandardAreaLSACount
fmOspfStandardAreaLSACount.description: OSPF Area LSA Count. The total number of link-state advertisements in this area's link-state database, excluding AS External LSA's.

fmOspfStandardAreaLSACksumSum.name: fmOspfStandardAreaLSACksumSum
fmOspfStandardAreaLSACksumSum.description: OSPF Area LSA Checksum Sum. The 32-bit unsigned sum of the link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this area's link-state database. This sum excludes external (LS type 5) link-state advertisements. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in a router's link state database, and to compare the link-state database of two routers.

fmOspfStandardStubAreaTable.name: fmOspfStandardStubAreaTable
fmOspfStandardStubAreaTable.description: The set of metrics that will be advertised by a default Area Border Router into a stub area

fmOspfStandardStubAreaID.name: fmOspfStandardStubAreaID
fmOspfStandardStubAreaID.description: OSPF Stub Area Id. The 32 bit identifier for the Stub Area. On creation, this can be derived from the instance.

fmOspfStandardStubTOS.name: fmOspfStandardStubTOS
fmOspfStandardStubTOS.description: OSPF Stub Area TOS. The Type of Service associated with the metric. On creation, this can be derived from the instance.

fmOspfStandardStubMetric.name: fmOspfStandardStubMetric
fmOspfStandardStubMetric.description: OSPF Stub Area Metric. The metric value applied at the indicated type of service. By default, this equals the least metric at the type of service among the interfaces to other areas.

fmOspfStandardStubStatus.name: fmOspfStandardStubStatus
fmOspfStandardStubStatus.description: OSPF Stub Area Status. This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent .

fmOspfStandardLsdbTable.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbTable
fmOspfStandardLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's Links State Database.

fmOspfStandardLsdbAreaId.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbAreaId
fmOspfStandardLsdbAreaId.description: OSPF Link State Database Area Id The OSPF Process's Links State Database.

fmOspfStandardLsdbType.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbType
fmOspfStandardLsdbType.description: OSPF Link State Database LS Type. The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.

fmOspfStandardLsdbLSID.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbLSID
fmOspfStandardLsdbLSID.description: OSPF Link State Database LS Id. The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP Address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

fmOspfStandardLsdbRouterId.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbRouterId
fmOspfStandardLsdbRouterId.description: OSPF Link State Database Router Id. The 32 bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

fmOspfStandardLsdbSequence.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbSequence
fmOspfStandardLsdbSequence.description: OSPF Link State Database Sequence. The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It is used to detect old and duplicate link state advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number the more recent the advertisement.

fmOspfStandardLsdbAge.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbAge
fmOspfStandardLsdbAge.description: OSPF Link State Database Age. This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

fmOspfStandardLsdbChecksum.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbChecksum
fmOspfStandardLsdbChecksum.description: OSPF Link State Database Checksum. This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

fmOspfStandardLsdbAdvertisement.name: fmOspfStandardLsdbAdvertisement
fmOspfStandardLsdbAdvertisement.description: OSPF Link State Database Advertisement. The entire Link State Advertisement, including its header.

fmOspfStandardAreaRangeTable.name: fmOspfStandardAreaRangeTable
fmOspfStandardAreaRangeTable.description: A range if IP addresses specified by an IP address/IP network mask pair. For example, class B address range of X.X.X.X with a network mask of 255.255.0.0 includes all IP addresses from X.X.0.0 to X.X.255.255.

fmOspfStandardAreaRangeAreaID.name: fmOspfStandardAreaRangeAreaID
fmOspfStandardAreaRangeAreaID.description: OSPF Area Range Area Id. The Area the Address Range is to be found within.

fmOspfStandardAreaRangeNet.name: fmOspfStandardAreaRangeNet
fmOspfStandardAreaRangeNet.description: OSPF Area Range Net. The IP Address of the Net or Subnet indicated by the range.

fmOspfStandardAreaRangeMask.name: fmOspfStandardAreaRangeMask
fmOspfStandardAreaRangeMask.description: OSPF Area Range Mask. The Subnet Mask that pertains to the Net or Subnet.

fmOspfStandardAreaRangeStatus.name: fmOspfStandardAreaRangeStatus
fmOspfStandardAreaRangeStatus.description: OSPF Area Range Status. This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

fmOspfStandardHostTable.name: fmOspfStandardHostTable
fmOspfStandardHostTable.description: The list of Hosts, and their metrics, that the router will advertise as host routes.

fmOspfStandardHostIpAddress.name: fmOspfStandardHostIpAddress
fmOspfStandardHostIpAddress.description: OSPF Host Ip Address. The IP Address of the Host.

fmOspfStandardHostTOS.name: fmOspfStandardHostTOS
fmOspfStandardHostTOS.description: OSPF Host TOS. The Type of Service of the route being configured.

fmOspfStandardHostMetric.name: fmOspfStandardHostMetric
fmOspfStandardHostMetric.description: OSPF Host Metric. The Metric to be advertised.

fmOspfStandardHostStatus.name: fmOspfStandardHostStatus
fmOspfStandardHostStatus.description: OSPF Host Status. This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

fmOspfStandardIfTable.name: fmOspfStandardIfTable
fmOspfStandardIfTable.description: The OSPF Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of OSPF.

fmOspfStandardIfIpAddress.name: fmOspfStandardIfIpAddress
fmOspfStandardIfIpAddress.description: OSPF Interface Ip Address. The IP address of this OSPF interface.

fmOspfStandardAddressLessIf.name: fmOspfStandardAddressLessIf
fmOspfStandardAddressLessIf.description: OSPF Interface Address Less If. For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

fmOspfStandardIfAreaId.name: fmOspfStandardIfAreaId
fmOspfStandardIfAreaId.description: OSPF Interface Area Id. A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

fmOspfStandardIfType.name: fmOspfStandardIfType
fmOspfStandardIfType.description: OSPF Interface Type. The OSPF interface type. By way of a default, this field may be intuited from the corresponding value of ifType. Broadcast LANs, such as Ethernet and IEEE 802.5, take the value 'broadcast', X.25, Frame Relay, and similar technologies take the value 'nbma', and links that are definitively point to point take the value 'pointToPoint'

fmOspfStandardIfAdminStat.name: fmOspfStandardIfAdminStat
fmOspfStandardIfAdminStat.description: OSPF Interface Administrative Status. The OSPF interface's administrative status. The value 'enabled' denotes that neighbor relationships may be formed on the interface, and the interface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPF.

fmOspfStandardIfRtrPriority.name: fmOspfStandardIfRtrPriority
fmOspfStandardIfRtrPriority.description: OSPF Interface Router Priority. The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their router id as a tie breaker

fmOspfStandardIfTransitDelay.name: fmOspfStandardIfTransitDelay
fmOspfStandardIfTransitDelay.description: OSPF Interface Transit Delay. The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.

fmOspfStandardIfRetransInterval.name: fmOspfStandardIfRetransInterval
fmOspfStandardIfRetransInterval.description: OSPF Interface Retransmit Interval. The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link-state request packets.

fmOspfStandardIfHelloInterval.name: fmOspfStandardIfHelloInterval
fmOspfStandardIfHelloInterval.description: OSPF Interface Hello Interval. The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

fmOspfStandardIfRtrDeadInterval.name: fmOspfStandardIfRtrDeadInterval
fmOspfStandardIfRtrDeadInterval.description: OSPF Interface Dead Interval. The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

fmOspfStandardIfPollInterval.name: fmOspfStandardIfPollInterval
fmOspfStandardIfPollInterval.description: OSPF Interface Poll Interval. The larger time interval, in seconds, between the Hello packets sent to an inactive non-broadcast multi- access neighbor.

fmOspfStandardIfState.name: fmOspfStandardIfState
fmOspfStandardIfState.description: OSPF Interface State. The OSPF Interface State.

fmOspfStandardIfDesignatedRouter.name: fmOspfStandardIfDesignatedRouter
fmOspfStandardIfDesignatedRouter.description: OSPF Interface Designated Router. The IP Address of the Designated Router.

fmOspfStandardIfBackupDesignatedRouter.name: fmOspfStandardIfBackupDesignatedRouter
fmOspfStandardIfBackupDesignatedRouter.description: OSPF Interface Backup Designated Router. The IP Address of the Backup Designated Router.

fmOspfStandardIfEvents.name: fmOspfStandardIfEvents
fmOspfStandardIfEvents.description: OSPF Interface Events. The number of times this OSPF interface has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

fmOspfStandardIfAuthKey.name: fmOspfStandardIfAuthKey
fmOspfStandardIfAuthKey.description: OSPF Interface Authentication Key. The Authentication Key. If the Area's Authorization Type is simplePassword, and the key length is shorter than 8 octets, the agent will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. When read, it always returns an Octet String of length zero.

fmOspfStandardIfMetricTable.name: fmOspfStandardIfMetricTable
fmOspfStandardIfMetricTable.description: The TOS metrics for a non-virtual interface identified by the interface index.

fmOspfStandardIfMetricIpAddress.name: fmOspfStandardIfMetricIpAddress
fmOspfStandardIfMetricIpAddress.description: OSPF Interface Metric Ip Address. The IP address of this OSPF interface. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.

fmOspfStandardIfMetricAddressLessIf.name: fmOspfStandardIfMetricAddressLessIf
fmOspfStandardIfMetricAddressLessIf.description: OSPF Interface Metric Address Less If. For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.

fmOspfStandardIfMetricTOS.name: fmOspfStandardIfMetricTOS
fmOspfStandardIfMetricTOS.description: OSPF Interface Metric TOS. The type of service metric being referenced. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.

fmOspfStandardIfMetricMetric.name: fmOspfStandardIfMetricMetric
fmOspfStandardIfMetricMetric.description: OSPF Interface Metric Metric. The metric of using this type of service on this interface. The default value of the TOS 0 Metric is 10^8 / ifSpeed. The value FFFF is distinguished to mean 'no route via this TOS.

fmOspfStandardIfMetricStatus.name: fmOspfStandardIfMetricStatus
fmOspfStandardIfMetricStatus.description: ID FMSIPOSPF Interface Metric Status. This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. he internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfTable.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfTable
fmOspfStandardVirtIfTable.description: Information about this router's virtual interfaces.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfAreaID.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfAreaID
fmOspfStandardVirtIfAreaID.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Area ID. The Transit Area that the Virtual Link traverses. By definition, this is not 0.0.0.0

fmOspfStandardVirtIfNeighbor.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfNeighbor
fmOspfStandardVirtIfNeighbor.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Neighbor. The Router ID of the Virtual Neighbor.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfTransitDelay.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfTransitDelay
fmOspfStandardVirtIfTransitDelay.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Transit Delay. The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link- state update packet over this interface.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfRetransInterval.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfRetransInterval
fmOspfStandardVirtIfRetransInterval.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Retransmit Interval. The number of seconds between link-state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and link-state request packets. This value should be well over the expected round-trip time.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfHelloInterval.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfHelloInterval
fmOspfStandardVirtIfHelloInterval.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Hello Interval. The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfRtrDeadInterval
fmOspfStandardVirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Router Dead Interval. The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before it's neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfState.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfState
fmOspfStandardVirtIfState.description: OSPF Virtual Interface State. OSPF virtual interface states.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfEvents.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfEvents
fmOspfStandardVirtIfEvents.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Events. The number of state changes or error events on this Virtual Link.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfAuthKey.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfAuthKey
fmOspfStandardVirtIfAuthKey.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Authentication Type. If Authentication Type is simplePassword, the device will left adjust and zero fill to 8 octets. When read, ospfVifAuthKey always returns a string of length zero.

fmOspfStandardVirtIfStatus.name: fmOspfStandardVirtIfStatus
fmOspfStandardVirtIfStatus.description: OSPF Virtual Interface Status. This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

fmOspfStandardNbrTable.name: fmOspfStandardNbrTable
fmOspfStandardNbrTable.description: A table of non-virtual neighbor information.

fmOspfStandardNbrIpAddress.name: fmOspfStandardNbrIpAddress
fmOspfStandardNbrIpAddress.description: OSPF Neighbor Ip Address. The IP address of this neighbor.

fmOspfStandardNbrAddressLessIndex.name: fmOspfStandardNbrAddressLessIndex
fmOspfStandardNbrAddressLessIndex.description: OSPF Neighbor Address Less Index. On an interface having an IP Address, zero. On addressless interfaces, the corresponding value of ifIndex in the Internet Standard MIB. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.

fmOspfStandardNbrRtrId.name: fmOspfStandardNbrRtrId
fmOspfStandardNbrRtrId.description: OSPF Neighbor Router Id. A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAddress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

fmOspfStandardNbrOptions.name: fmOspfStandardNbrOptions
fmOspfStandardNbrOptions.description: OSPF Neighbor Options. A Bit Mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Bit 0, if set, indicates that the area accepts and operates on external information; if zero, it is a stub area. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric.

fmOspfStandardNbrPriority.name: fmOspfStandardNbrPriority
fmOspfStandardNbrPriority.description: OSPF Neighbor Priority. The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.

fmOspfStandardNbrState.name: fmOspfStandardNbrState
fmOspfStandardNbrState.description: OSPF Neighbor State. The State of the relationship with this Neighbor.

fmOspfStandardNbrEvents.name: fmOspfStandardNbrEvents
fmOspfStandardNbrEvents.description: OSPF Neighbor Events. The number of times this neighbor relationship has changed state, or an error has occurred.

fmOspfStandardNbrLSRetransQLen.name: fmOspfStandardNbrLSRetransQLen
fmOspfStandardNbrLSRetransQLen.description: OSPF Neighbor LS Retransmit Queue Length. The current length of the retransmission queue.

fmOspfStandardNBMANbrStatus.name: fmOspfStandardNBMANbrStatus
fmOspfStandardNBMANbrStatus.description: OSPF Neighbor Status. This variable displays the validity or invalidity of the entry. Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative. The internal effect (row removal) is implementation dependent.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrTable.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrTable
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrTable.description: A table of virtual neighbor information.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrArea.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrArea
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrArea.description: OSPF Virtual Neighbor Area. The Transit Area Identifier.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrRtrId.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrRtrId
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrRtrId.description: OSPF Virtual Neighbor Router Id. A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrIpAddr.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrIpAddr
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrIpAddr.description: OSPF Virtual Neighbor Ip Address. The IP address this Virtual Neighbor is using.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrOptions.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrOptions
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrOptions.description: OSPF Virtual Neighbor Options. A bit map corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Thus, Bit 1, if set, indicates that the neighbor supports Type of Service Routing; if zero, no metrics other than TOS 0 are in use by the neighbor.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrState.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrState
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrState.description: OSPF Virtual Neighbor State. The state of the Virtual Neighbor Relationship.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrEvents.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrEvents
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrEvents.description: OSPF Virtual Neighbor Events. The number of times this virtual link has changed its state, or an error has occurred.

fmOspfStandardVirtNbrLSRetransQLen.name: fmOspfStandardVirtNbrLSRetransQLen
fmOspfStandardVirtNbrLSRetransQLen.description: OSPF Virtual Neighbor LS Retransmit Queue Length. The current length of the retransmission queue.

fmhEqIdSerialNbEncodingType.description: Type de codage du numero de serie de l'equipement

fmsInArpVpConnX121.description: X121 address on which an inverse ARP has been done.

fmsInArpVpVirtualPortId.name: fmsInArpVpVirtualPortId
fmsInArpVpVirtualPortId.description: Virtual Port Identifier of the Inverse ARP statistic.

fmsInArpVpOutRequests.name: fmsInArpVpOutRequests
fmsInArpVpOutRequests.description: Number of Inverse ARP request sent on this connection.

fmsInArpVpInRequests.description: Number of Inverse ARP request received on the connection.

fmsInArpVpInverseArpStatus.description: State of the inverse ARP resolution.

fmsBootPClientStatus.name: fmsBootPClientStatus
fmsBootPClientStatus.description: The value of this object identifies result of BootP transaction.

fmsBootPClientFileName.name: fmsBootPClientFileName
fmsBootPClientFileName.description: The value of this object identifies the file name received after bootreply reception.

fmsBootPClientServerIpAddr.name: fmsBootPClientServerIpAddr
fmsBootPClientServerIpAddr.description: The value of this object identifies the server IP address which has contacted bootp client manager.

fmsBootPClientGatewayIpAddr.name: fmsBootPClientGatewayIpAddr
fmsBootPClientGatewayIpAddr.description: The value of this object identifies the gateway IP address. This field is used in optional cross-gateway booting.

fmsBootPRelayTable.name: fmsBootPRelayTable
fmsBootPRelayTable.description: This table describes the parameters used in BootP Relay mode. It gives statistics of BootP packets transfers.

fmsBootPRelayVirtualPortId.name: fmsBootPRelayVirtualPortId
fmsBootPRelayVirtualPortId.description: The value of this object identifies the Virtual Port Identifier of BootP Relay statistic.

fmsBootPRelayRelayedPkts.name: fmsBootPRelayRelayedPkts
fmsBootPRelayRelayedPkts.description: The value of this object identifies the number of packets routed by gateway in the case of BootP Relay mode.

fmsBootPRelayDroppedPkts.name: fmsBootPRelayDroppedPkts
fmsBootPRelayDroppedPkts.description: The value of this object identifies the number of destroyed packets.

fmsBootPRelayRecRequests.name: fmsBootPRelayRecRequests
fmsBootPRelayRecRequests.description: The value of this object identifies the number of received packets.

fmsBootPRelayRecReplies.name: fmsBootPRelayRecReplies
fmsBootPRelayRecReplies.description: The value of this object identifies the number of received responses.

frxStateChange.name: frxStateChange
frxStateChange.description: A frxStateChange trap signifies that a outstanding events takes place. This event is not in frxNodeStateChange, frxLineStateChange, frxLoadAndTrafficEvent, frxManagementEvent, frxServicesStateChange.

frxNodeStateChange.name: frxNodeStateChange
frxNodeStateChange.description: A frxNodeStateChange trap signifies that a state changing takes place in the equipment or in a module.

frxLineStateChange.name: frxLineStateChange
frxLineStateChange.description: A frxLineStateChange trap signifies that a state changing takes place over a SLL (Switched Logical Link), over the level 2 or 3 protocol of the line. It can indicate a charge overflow of the line.

frxLoadAndTrafficEvent.name: frxLoadAndTrafficEvent
frxLoadAndTrafficEvent.description: A frxLoadAndTrafficEvent trap signifies that the maximum threshold, like the number of virtual circuits, the data frame rejection threshold ..., is reached.

frxManagementEvent.name: frxManagementEvent
frxManagementEvent.description: A frxManagementEvent trap signifies that a configuration changing takes place or someone behaves on the system.

frxServicesStateChange.name: frxServicesStateChange
frxServicesStateChange.description: A frxServicesStateChange trap signifies that something about additional services (securized virtual circuit, compression, regrouping frames) takes place.

fdpIdentPhysPortId.name: fdpIdentPhysPortId
fdpIdentPhysPortId.description: The value of this object is the physical port number. This value may be modified only if fdpIdentPhysPortState is 'notConfigured', 'up' or 'down'.

fdpIdentPhysPortState.name: fdpIdentPhysPortState
fdpIdentPhysPortState.description: The value of this object is the state of the physical port identified by fdpIdentPhysPortId.

fdpCtrlCommand.name: fdpCtrlCommand
fdpCtrlCommand.description: The value of this object is the desired state of the physical port described in fdpIdentPhysPortId. The equipment answers always with the value 'ready' to a GetRequest on this object.

fdpCtrlDiagCode.name: fdpCtrlDiagCode
fdpCtrlDiagCode.description: The value of this object is the result of the last SET on fdpCtrlCommand.

fdpTestLoopBackType.name: fdpTestLoopBackType
fdpTestLoopBackType.description: The value of this object is the desired loop type run on the physical port described in fdpIdentPhysPortId.

fdpTestOutputPacketsCount.name: fdpTestOutputPacketsCount
fdpTestOutputPacketsCount.description: The value of this object is the maximum number of messages to be sent during the test. '0' means 'infinite'.

fdpTestMaxDuration.name: fdpTestMaxDuration
fdpTestMaxDuration.description: The value of this object is the maximum duration of the test in seconds.

fdpTestCommand.name: fdpTestCommand
fdpTestCommand.description: The value of this object permits to start or stop the loop test described in fdpTestLoopBackType, fdpTestOutputPacketsCount and fdpTestMaxDuration. The equipment answers always with the value 'ready' to a GetRequest on this object.

fdpTestDiagCode.name: fdpTestDiagCode
fdpTestDiagCode.description: The value of this object is the result of the last SET on fdpTestCommand.

fdpTestState.name: fdpTestState
fdpTestState.description: The value of this object is the state of the last test started.

fdpTestOutPktsCounter.name: fdpTestOutPktsCounter
fdpTestOutPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of messages sent during the test.

fdpTestInPktsCounter.name: fdpTestInPktsCounter
fdpTestInPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of messages received during the test.

fdpTestInErrPktsCounter.name: fdpTestInErrPktsCounter
fdpTestInErrPktsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of incorrect messages received during the test.

fdpTestInErrOctetsCounter.name: fdpTestInErrOctetsCounter
fdpTestInErrOctetsCounter.description: The value of this object is the number of incorrect characters received during the test.

fdpModCommand.name: fdpModCommand
fdpModCommand.description: The value of this object permits to open or close a session with a modem connected on the physical port described in fdpIdentPhysPortId. The equipment answers always with the value 'ready' to a GetRequest on this object.

fdpModControlData.name: fdpModControlData
fdpModControlData.description: The value of this object is AT Commands to be sent to the modem

fdpModDiagCode.name: fdpModDiagCode
fdpModDiagCode.description: The value of this object is the result of the last SET on fdpModCommand or fdpModControlData. The value 'modemData' means that the modem has sent one or several responses which may be seen in fdpModResponseTable.

fdpModResponseTable.name: fdpModResponseTable
fdpModResponseTable.description: This table contents the result of the last AT commands described in fdpModControlData.

fdpModRespEltNum.name: fdpModRespEltNum
fdpModRespEltNum.description: The value of this object is the identifier of one text line of a response of the modem.

fdpModRespElement.name: fdpModRespElement
fdpModRespElement.description: The value of this object contains the ASCII characters of this text line.

cmeClearX121Address.name: cmeClearX121Address
cmeClearX121Address.description: The value of this object is the X121 address of the remote equipment.

cmeClearCallUserData.name: cmeClearCallUserData
cmeClearCallUserData.description: The value of this object is the call user data send to the Compac management function.

cmeClearEvent.name: cmeClearEvent
cmeClearEvent.description: The value of this object is the type of X25 failed connection.

cmeClearCause.name: cmeClearCause
cmeClearCause.description: The value of this object is the X25 clear cause number.

cmeClearDiag.name: cmeClearDiag
cmeClearDiag.description: The value of this object is the X25 clear diagnostic number.

cmeClearTimeStamp.name: cmeClearTimeStamp
cmeClearTimeStamp.description: The value of this object is the sysUpTime at last disconnection time.
